Kent Sprouse, 42, was sent to death row for a 2002 shootout at a Texas convenience store that killed Ferris Police Officer Harry Steinfeldt III .
He shot and killed a customer, Pedro Moreno, 38, at a gas station in 2002 .
A jury decided in 2004 that he should be put to death .
In 2004, a jury decided that Sprouse was mentally ill and should be spared the death penalty .